Chris FreeMan craps pit boss poor CS
Craps Personnel Review:

We travel several times a year to Vegas and it’s a hit and miss at South point casino.

Visited 10/12/23 @ about 4pmish.

Played craps. Box man Chris Freeman.

Every shooter playing was throwing the dice properly , with two dice hitting the back wall.. occasionally one coming short. Chris FREEMAN was on top of each and EVERY inadvertent throw where one dice may have gone short , with a reprimand to the shooter that both dice has to hit the back wall.. he is correct at that, and as mentioned 95-100% of all throws were proper. But as soon as one of those inadvertent short throws occur, he was on it to reprimand and remind the shooter of the back board. Everyone, was getting annoyed at this, so apologies offered to him.

A consistent reprimand and reminder was not necessary towards the customers and myself for an inadvertent short throw here and there. It appears he was treating everyone like children which was very disrespectful.

His demeanor and scolding was not necessary every single time an inadvertent short throw on one dice occurred.. he definitely was taking the fun out of the game as expressions on players faces dictated.. I eventually took down my bets and sought another table..

I took a break to play cards. I returned to find my brother on a table. As I approached, he was upset and was taking down all his bets after being told he was shooting for awhile. He told me the box man was doing the same thing about reprimanding each throw, even if one of the dice was just short of the wall .. he mentioned Chris FREEMAN just sat in and relieved the current box man. He exercised that reprimand as soon as the first throw with one dice coming short. My brother took down all his bets along with two other shooters who saw Freeman’s actions.

It’s understandable he needs both dice to hit the back wall, but sometimes mis throws and inadvertent throws , results in a dice or two coming short. Not like it’s a consistent action where his reprimands would be justified.

That just was not happening, although each time he “reminded “ ( which was unnecessary ) was verbilzed in a reprimand form, which treated the customers like kids and especially taking the fun out of the game…Chris FREEMAN is VERY POOR in offering a fun experience in gambling at the south point..

JeffersonKid
Albuquerque, New Mexico
45 contributions
Yes they provide free drinks. Waitresses serve the table games more frequently and less so on slot machines. Tips are NOT required but $1 US per drink is a standard. You pay full price for drinks at bars ($8 US for a beer) unless you get on the video poker machines at the bar (standard is put in $20 US to start but you don't have to bet all of that to get the free drink). Slot servers appear about every half hour. South Point is a very good casino and tries to be customer friendly.
